According to [JB] (09/09/87, 2nd edition), [DP] (10/09/87) and [OESP] (13/09/87)
sources, the original rule of 1987 Brazilian Championship stated that the 12 best
teams of White and Blue Modules would be qualified to 1988 Second Level, but it
is unclear if these teams were 6 from each module or an overall classification
or any other criteria would be adopted.

These rules, however, were not applied, since the composition of 1988 First
and Second Levels were defined under other criteria.


